<p><ent>Scar</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Scar
<hw>Scar</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Scot. <ets>scar</ets>,
<ets>scaur</ets>, Icel. <ets>sker</ets> a skerry, an isolated rock in
the sea; akin to Dan. <ets>skiaer</ets>, Sw. <ets>sk⟦aum⟧r</ets>. Cf.
<er>Skerry</er>.]</ety> <def>An isolated or protruding rock; a steep,
rocky eminence; a bare place on the side of a mountain or steep bank of
earth.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>scaur</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O sweet and far, from cliff and <qex>scar</qex>,⟦br⟧
The horns of Elfland faintly blowing.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scar</ent>⟦br⟧

